channeldata.description: Viridis is a Python library for tree data and algorithms. It is named after _Morelia viridis_, the green tree python. It is compatible with and tested with 100% coverage on Python 3.5.
channeldata.summary: Port of the new matplotlib color maps ('viridis' - the default -, 'magma', 'plasma' and 'inferno') to R. matplotlib is a popular plotting library for python. These color maps are designed in such a way that they will analytically be perfectly perceptually-uniform, both in regular form and also when converted to black-and-white. They are also designed to be perceived by readers with the most common form of color blindness.
